As Platform Specialty Prods Cor (PAH) Stock Price Rose, Mad River Investors Has Lowered Its Holding by $852,300; Davidson Investment Advisors Decreased Its Holding in Martin Marietta Materials (MLM) by $2.74 Million


					

						July 25, 2017 - By Vivian Park

Mad River Investors decreased its stake in Platform Specialty Prods Cor (PAH) by 38.04% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Mad River Investors sold 94,700 shares as the company’s stock rose 0.60% with the market. The hedge fund held 154,275 shares of the major chemicals company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $1.51 million, down from 248,975 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Mad River Investors who had been investing in Platform Specialty Prods Cor for a number of months, seems to be less bullish one the $3.71B market cap company. The stock increased 3.86% or $0.5 during the last trading session, reaching $13.46. About shares traded. Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH) has risen 48.23% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 31.53% the S&P500.
Davidson Investment Advisors decreased its stake in Martin Marietta Materials Inc (MLM) by 27.27% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Davidson Investment Advisors sold 12,420 shares as the company’s stock rose 4.98% with the market. The institutional investor held 33,130 shares of the basic industries company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $7.34 million, down from 45,550 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Davidson Investment Advisors who had been investing in Martin Marietta Materials Inc for a number of months, seems to be less bullish one the $14.21B market cap company. The stock increased 1.04% or $2.33 during the last trading session, reaching $227. About shares traded. Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM) has risen 23.49% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 6.79% the S&P500.







Mad River Investors, which manages about $262.29 million and $77.47M US Long portfolio, upped its stake in Dish Network Corp (NASDAQ:DISH) by 5,950 shares to 47,025 shares, valued at $2.72M in 2016Q4, according to the filing. 
Among 9 analysts covering Platform Specialty Products Corporation (NYSE:PAH), 6 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 3 Hold. Therefore 67% are positive. Platform Specialty Products Corporation had 20 analyst reports since August 17, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The stock of Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH) has “Buy” rating given on Monday, August 22 by Roth Capital. The company was maintained on Tuesday, August 16 by Barclays Capital. On Tuesday, September 13 the stock rating was maintained by Nomura with “Neutral”. On Monday, January 30 the stock rating was initiated by Morgan Stanley with “Equal-Weight”. The stock of Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH) has “Neutral” rating given on Thursday, December 3 by Credit Suisse. The stock of Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH) earned “Buy” rating by TH Capital on Monday, August 22. The firm earned “Equal Weight” rating on Wednesday, October 5 by Barclays Capital. As per Tuesday, June 13, the company rating was maintained by Nomura. Bank of America initiated the stock with “Buy” rating in Wednesday, March 9 report. The company was maintained on Thursday, September 29 by UBS.
More important recent Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH) news were published by: Reuters.com which released: “Morning News Call – India, July 25” on July 25, 2017, also Economictimes.Indiatimes.com published article titled: “UPL explores bid for Platform Specialty agrochem unit: Sources”, Reuters.com published: “Exclusive: India’s UPL explores bid for Platform Specialty agrochem unit – sources” on July 24, 2017. More interesting news about Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH) was released by: Law360.com and their article: “Deals Rumor Mill: Spotify, UPL, Nestle” with publication date: July 24, 2017.
Analysts await Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH) to report earnings on August, 14. They expect $0.18 earnings per share, up 12.50% or $0.02 from last year’s $0.16 per share. PAH’s profit will be $49.61 million for 18.69 P/E if the $0.18 EPS becomes a reality. After $0.16 actual earnings per share reported by Platform Specialty Products Corp for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts 12.50% EPS growth. 
Investors sentiment decreased to 1.09 in 2016 Q4. Its down 1.48, from 2.57 in 2016Q3. It dived, as 37 investors sold PAH shares while 41 reduced holdings. 22 funds opened positions while 63 raised stakes. 235.89 million shares or 2.83% more from 229.41 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Moreover, Legal General Public Ltd has 0% invested in Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH). Blackrock Institutional Na reported 5.19M shares. 124,327 were accumulated by Walleye Trading Limited Liability Corporation. Profund Advsr Limited Liability Corporation owns 17,083 shares. California Pub Employees Retirement reported 76,400 shares. Gabelli Funds Llc has 0.01% invested in Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH) for 115,000 shares. Gamco Invsts Et Al invested in 60,000 shares. Susquehanna Intl Gru Llp owns 98,352 shares for 0% of their portfolio. 53,445 were accumulated by First Tru Advisors Ltd Partnership. Kings Point Capital Mgmt accumulated 37,178 shares or 0.09% of the stock. Independent holds 103,775 shares. Glenview Cap Mgmt Limited Co holds 13.85M shares or 0.92% of its portfolio. Moreover, Sei Invests has 0% invested in Platform Specialty Products Corp (NYSE:PAH). Invesco Limited holds 0% or 338,309 shares in its portfolio. Wellington Mgmt Gru Ltd Liability Partnership reported 30.37M shares.
Analysts await Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM) to report earnings on August, 1. They expect $2.40 earnings per share, up 26.32% or $0.50 from last year’s $1.9 per share. MLM’s profit will be $150.24M for 23.65 P/E if the $2.40 EPS becomes a reality. After $0.67 actual earnings per share reported by Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts 258.21% EPS growth. 
Since February 17, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 7 selling transactions for $7.14 million activity. Nye C Howard also sold $2.45 million worth of Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM) shares. 6,000 shares were sold by MCDONALD WILLIAM E, worth $1.32 million. 1,391 shares were sold by McCunniff Donald A., worth $334,071. Guzzo Dana F. sold $198,330 worth of stock. LLOYD ANNE H had sold 6,472 shares worth $1.55 million. 3,000 shares were sold by PEREZ LAREE E, worth $656,952.
Davidson Investment Advisors, which manages about $1.17 billion and $701.68 million US Long portfolio, upped its stake in Colony Starwood Homes by 13,344 shares to 201,229 shares, valued at $5.79M in 2016Q4, according to the filing. It also increased its holding in Alphabet Inc Cl C by 1,101 shares in the quarter, for a total of 28,041 shares, and has risen its stake in Sprouts Farmers Market Inc (NASDAQ:SFM). 
Investors sentiment decreased to 0.98 in 2016 Q4. Its down 0.24, from 1.22 in 2016Q3. It turned negative, as 46 investors sold MLM shares while 165 reduced holdings. 65 funds opened positions while 141 raised stakes. 60.58 million shares or 0.58% less from 60.93 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. State Of Tennessee Treasury Department invested in 92,034 shares or 0.11% of the stock. Laffer owns 7,676 shares. Lodge Hill Ltd Liability Co owns 7.77% invested in Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM) for 274,900 shares. Cookson Peirce Co owns 81,275 shares for 2.49% of their portfolio. First Citizens Retail Bank And Trust invested in 3,065 shares. 2,039 were accumulated by New Century Inv Mgmt. Raymond James Assoc holds 0.02% of its portfolio in Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM) for 28,408 shares. Franklin Street Nc holds 50,015 shares. Moreover, Andra Ap has 0.01% invested in Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM). Moreover, Cetera Advisor Netwr Ltd Liability Corporation has 0.01% invested in Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM). Products Prtnrs Ltd invested 0.39% in Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM). Fcm Invs Tx holds 0.02% or 150 shares. First Interstate Savings Bank stated it has 0% of its portfolio in Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM). Chevy Chase Tru accumulated 56,616 shares. The United Kingdom-based Barclays Public Limited Co has invested 0.01% in Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM).
More news for Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. (NYSE:MLM) were recently published by: Globenewswire.com, which released: “Martin Marietta Materials, Inc. to Broadcast Second Quarter 2017 Conference …” on July 20, 2017. Gurufocus.com‘s article titled: “Renaissance Investment Group LLC Buys Martin Marietta Materials Inc, Sells …” and published on July 13, 2017 is yet another important article.


